(Numbers modulo 5 are 0,1,2,3,4. Their squares modulo 5 are 0,1,4,4,1. Thus, a square can only be 5q, 5q+1, or 5q+4. It can never be 5q+2) Tj
T* (or 5q+3.) Tj
